Marketplace Support Specialist<br /> United States,         Europe, Remote Possible<br />
<br /> <br /> We are looking for an exceptional Marketplace         Support Specialist to join the SUMO team (support.mozilla.com) and help us deliver top quality user support for our         new Marketplace.&nbsp;You should be         someone who thrives on providing email support but doesn&rsquo;t         hesitate to jump into other channels such as forums, chat, and         Twitter. You&rsquo;re a great match if you possess         fantastic trouble-shooting skills, are driven to help customers         and have the ability to dive deep into a new product to learn it         inside and out.<br /> <br /> As part of Mozilla, the Marketplace Support         Specialist will lead our email support, providing feedback and         input in order to improve support processes and policies. The         selected candidate will also serve as interface between         customers and internal teams like Product, Engineering, QA,         Content Management, etc.<br /> <br /> Since the SUMO team is geographically         distributed across the United States (from east to west) and         Europe, we believe the successful candidate could work from any         of these time zones. Of course, working with an online team         means that the Marketplace Support Specialist is flexible, hard         working, and a true team player who communicates proactively         both verbally and in writing.<br /> <br /> The ideal candidate should be willing to         start the job as a part time contractor and be flexible to         increase the amount of dedicated time to a full time schedule as         the project gains popularity.&nbsp;<br />
<br /> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;         &nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> Responsibilities:<br /> * Respond to incoming Marketplace support         email requests<br /> * Interact with Product management,         Engineering and QA for both problem escalation and to keep up to         date on new features<br /> * Help to polish contact policies and quality         standards<br /> * Collaborate with Content Manager to improve         help articles<br /> <br /> Requirements:<br /> * Excellent customer service skills &ndash; the         ability to be empathetic, accurate, compassionate, responsive,         resourceful, and conscientious. Outstanding written and oral         communication skills <br /> * Ability to evaluate, troubleshoot, and         follow-up on customer issues as well as replicate and document         for further escalation&nbsp;<br /> * Ability to think and execute resourcefully,         with minimal supervision<br /> * Ability to learn quickly and adapt in a         fast-paced start-up environment<br /> * Understanding of web technologies and         Mozilla's core values<br /> <br /> Skills Desired:<br /> * Experience with paid or volunteer technical         customer support. Experience with eCommerce support is a big         plus.<br /> * Passionate about Firefox, Mozilla, and open         technologies<br /> * Participating and contributing to open         source projects a huge plus<br /> * Knowledge of a second           language (Spanish, German, French)<br /><br />&nbsp;
